<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,311,498]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
All six specimens showed 
<number box="[508,523,352,378]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.0">2</number>
rod-shaped macroplacoids within the pharyngeal bulb. Body size ranged from 
<number box="[151,278,392,418]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="500.5" valueMax="627.0" valueMin="374.0">374 to 627</number>
μm, mean 
<number box="[411,455,392,418]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="512.0">512</number>
μm (SD 
<number box="[565,598,392,418]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="83.0">83</number>
). The species has been cited for Europe, Asia and 
<collectingCountry box="[1196,1301,392,418]" name="United States of America" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">America</collectingCountry>
. In the Iberian Peninsula, it has been recorded for 
<collectingCountry box="[632,699,432,458]" name="Spain" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Guil" box="[716,844,432,458]" pageId="16" pageNumber="29" refString="Guil, N. (2002) Diversity and distribution of tardigrades (Bilateria, Tardigrada) from the Iberian Peninsula, Balearic Islands and Chafarinas Islands. Graellsia, 58 (2), 75 - 94." type="journal article" year="2002">
Guil 
<number box="[780,844,432,458]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[865,1155,432,457]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Isohypsibius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="marcellinoi">
<emphasis box="[865,1155,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Isohypsibius marcellinoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from LF samples in 
<number box="[282,297,472,498]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
sampling points (Table 
<number box="[580,596,472,498]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.0">3</number>
).
</paragraph>
